HEADWORD: Ergotine
<hw>Er"go*tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A powerful
astringent alkaloid extracted from ergot as a brown, amorphous, bitter
substance. It is used to produce contraction of the uterus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ergotism</ent>⟦br⟧
